[1] WHO update
Date: Mon 22 Dec 2014
Source: The Economic Times [edited]
http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/articleshow/45610199.cms


More than 7500 people have now died from the Ebola virus, as the number of cases climbs towards 20 000, the World Health Organisation said today [22 Dec 2014].

The UN health agency reported that as of 20 Dec 2014, 19 340 people had been infected with the deadly virus in Guinea, Liberia and Sierra Leone, and that 7518 of them had died.

The death toll in other countries remained the same: 6 in Mali, one in the United States and 8 in Nigeria, which was declared Ebola-free in October 2014...

