[5] Region: Nigerian university re-admits 100 students from Ebola ravaged countries
Date: Sun 21 Dec 2014
Source: AllAfrica, Daily Independent (Lagos) report [edited]
http://allafrica.com/stories/201412220761.html


Nigeria: OAU re-admits 100 students from Ebola ravaged countries
----------------------------------------------------------------
Foreign students from countries with Ebola virus disease (EVD), numbering about 100, who were screened and cleared of having Ebola virus, were readmitted into the Obafemi Awolowo University (OAU), Ile-Ife, Osun State. The screening was conducted with the assistance of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs and Department of Immigration Service and clearance given to all those who were screened before they were re-admitted into the school. The re-admitted students had returned to campus to continue their studies.

Vice chancellor of the university, Professor Bamitale Omole, said [the decision to readmit the foreign students] ... was part of measures through which the management ensured that the virus would not spread to the campus...

[byline: Gbenga Faturoti]

